Key Match Events: Keyonte George dropped 33 points and nine assists to tie a career-high
The Jazz scored at least 30 points in each quarter of the game
Utah set a season-high with 35 assists and 16 three-pointers
The Jazz committed a season-low 12 turnovers
Pre-Game Insights: The Utah Jazz had struggled on the offensive end of the floor to open the 2024-25 season
Coming into the game, Utah owned the 30th-ranked offense due to cold shooting and turnover struggles
Post-Match Reflections: Keyonte George said, 'We wanted to come out and show that we can compete at a high level, play together, and play the right way'
Coach Will Hardy added, 'The ball was really moving around, they executed really well on the offensive side of the ball. It was a team win, everybody had moments where they stepped up'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Jazz were in a rhythm from the opening tip
Collins played more at the four position next to Drew Eubanks, thus opening him up for opportunities to attack mismatches
Williams finished with 11 points, five rebounds, and four assists, with the majority of his buckets coming off of cuts to the basket and aggressive drives
